() Tj
T*
(Final Version One External Interface Blueprint) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Version one should expose three distinct external surfaces:) Tj
T*
(- a public-safe read/query surface for explorers, wallets, merchants, and analytics tools) Tj
T*
(- a local authenticated RPC and event surface for exchanges, custodians, hosted providers, and) Tj
T*
(the Atho desktop app itself) Tj
T*
(- an indexer or query layer for read-heavy and historical workloads) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(What must exist in v1:) Tj
T*
(- chain status) Tj
T*
(- blocks) Tj
T*
(- tx lookup) Tj
T*
(- address summary and history) Tj
T*
(- UTXO lookup) Tj
T*
(- tx broadcast) Tj
T*
(- sync and readiness) Tj
T*
(- clear confirmation and reorg semantics) Tj
T*
(- stable response contracts) Tj
T*
(- integration docs) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(What should stay local-only:) Tj
T*
(- wallet unlock and mutation) Tj
T*
(- node lifecycle control) Tj
T*
(- network switch) Tj
T*
(- raw operator diagnostics) Tj
T*
(- peer control) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(What third parties should build against:) Tj
T*
(- explorers and analytics: query/indexer API) Tj
T*
(- wallets: query/indexer plus broadcast) Tj
T*
(- exchanges and custodians: self-hosted local RPC plus event stream and query layer) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(What should be standardized first:) Tj
T*
(- chain id and network names) Tj
T*
(- tx, block, address, and UTXO objects) Tj
T*
(- response envelopes and error codes) Tj
T*
(- status and confirmation semantics) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(What should wait until later:) Tj
T*
(- giant public debug surfaces) Tj
T*
(- rich public operator telemetry) Tj
T*
(- overcomplicated global streaming guarantees) Tj
T*
(- advanced search systems) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(How to make the ecosystem easy to build around from day one:) Tj
T*
(- keep the contracts boring) Tj
T*
(- keep the safety boundaries hard) Tj
T*
(- keep the docs honest) Tj
T*
(- keep public query load away from consensus hot paths) Tj
T*
(- keep local operator and wallet actions clearly separated from public builder surfaces) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
ET
endstream
